<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900606-0097</DOCNO><DOCID>900606-0097.</DOCID><HL>   Security Pacific Corp.   Ex-Aide Is Sentenced   In Drug-Money Case</HL><DATE>06/06/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   SPC</CO><IN>BANKS (BNK)</IN><GV>INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS)</GV><LP>   LOS ANGELES -- A former supervisory officer of SecurityPacific National Bank's central vault, 27-year-old Jose O.Lopez, was sentenced Monday to 46 months in prison forconspiracy in a drug-money laundering operation.   Also sentenced for the same offense was Geno Apicella, 27,to 37 months in prison. Both men pleaded guilty Feb. 28 tothe conspiracy charges, which came after an undercoverinvestigation by Internal Revenue Service special agents andinternal investigators of Security Pacific National Bank, aunit of Los Angeles-based Security Pacific Corp.</LP><TEXT>   During the four-month investigation, an IRS undercoveragent posing as a money man for narcotics traffickers gave$364,000 to be laundered through Security Pacific by thegroup, which Mr. Lopez headed.   In addition to Messrs. Lopez and Apicella, five otherdefendants pleaded guilty to conspiracy and were previouslysentenced.</TEXT></DOC>